<LEADPARA>  (check) Has Andrew Lloyd Webber sold out? Not exactly, but he has sold the
rights to his musicals plus 30 percent of his entertainment company to
Polygram Records for a tidy sum. "Tidy" in this case means a neatly stacked
$131.5 million.;    (check) John Adams' opera, "The Death of Klinghoffer,"
will be previewed on NPR Aug. 31 at 1:30 p.m. The work, recorded in March,
will have its U.S. premiere next month at the Brooklyn Academy of Music. It's
about the 1985 hijacking of the Achille Lauro and the murder of Leon
Klinghoffer.  </LEADPARA>
